<Layout title="Insurance Agents · Florida Insurance Agent Partner Hub — Homeowners HO-3, Hurricane Wind, NFIP Flood, Condo HO-6, Citizens Property &amp; Mortgage Lender Requirements" description="Florida insurance agent partner hub educating buyers, homeowners, and condo unit owners on what insurance agents do in real estate transactions: homeowners insurance HO-3 standard all-risk dwelling or HO-5 premier all-risk policy selection; hurricane and windstorm coverage in Florida as separate peril through private admitted carriers or Citizens Property Insurance Corporation as state-backed insurer of last resort; NFIP National Flood Insurance Program coverage through FEMA at FloodSmart.gov with maximum $250000 dwelling coverage and $100000 contents coverage or private flood alternatives offering higher limits; condo HO-6 unit-owner policy with loss assessment coverage critical post-Surfside collapse June 2021 and Florida SB 4-D milestone inspection structural integrity reserve study and reserve funding requirements; dwelling fire DP-3 for investment property and rental units; umbrella liability layered above auto and homeowners primary policies for $1M to $5M+ additional liability; wind mitigation inspection coordination for Florida-specific premium discounts on hip roof, opening protection impact-rated windows or shutters, roof-to-wall connection straps, secondary water resistance, and roof covering compliance with Florida Building Code; hurricane deductible structure as percentage of dwelling coverage commonly 2 percent 5 percent or 10 percent separate from standard all-other-perils deductible triggered by National Hurricane Center named-storm declaration; Four-Point Inspection for properties 25-30+ years old covering roof electrical plumbing HVAC condition assessment; and binder issuance at closing meeting mortgage lender requirements for 12 months prepaid insurance plus initial escrow reserve. Florida insurance market context: substantial market disruption 2022-2024 with private carrier withdrawals, Citizens Property Insurance growth to over 1.2 million policies at peak, and legislative reforms under Florida SB 2A 2022 special session establishing Reinsurance to Assist Policyholders RAP program and SB 7052 2023. Insurance agent types: independent agents representing multiple admitted carriers; captive agents with single-carrier appointments at State Farm Allstate Farmers Liberty Mutual Nationwide; surplus lines brokers placing coverage with non-admitted E&S carriers for hard-to-place coastal and older home risks; insurance brokers working as client-side fiduciary; direct writers Geico Progressive USAA Esurance. Florida agent credentials: CPCU Chartered Property Casualty Underwriter through The Institutes; CIC Certified Insurance Counselor and CRM Certified Risk Manager and CISR Certified Insurance Service Representative through The National Alliance; AAI Accredited Adviser in Insurance and ARM Associate in Risk Management through The Institutes; FAIA Florida Association of Insurance Agents and IIABA Independent Insurance Agents of Florida trade associations. Partner-as-borrower CTA at bottom routing insurance agents to /professional-services/ hub for multi-source income mortgage qualifying paths covering W-2 plus commission plus book-of-business renewals plus bonus variable compensation under Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 variable income framework, agency principals with K-1 partnership income under B3-3.4-02 partnership documentation." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/insurance-agents/">
  <div class="pia-scope" set:html={piaBody} />
</Layout>

